original_title: Vegan Missouri firefighter battles flaming truck loaded with beef on first day | Fox News
article_summary:
Vegan Firefighter Battles Flaming Truck Carrying 40,000 Pounds of Ribeye Steaks in Missouri Fire

A vegan firefighter, Jenna Ulrich, responded to her first fire at the Doolittle Rural Fire Protection District in Missouri, where she extinguished a tractor-trailer carrying 40,000 pounds of ribeye steaks that caught fire on Interstate 174 eastbound. Despite the unique challenge, the steaks were a total loss.</s>
